<Q>thoroughly acquainted with their mi|&s;erable, poor and mean circum&s;tances, they would readily &s;ubmit to whatever he &s;hould think them capable of doing.</Q><NOTE PLACE="marg">MS in files</NOTE>
They were al&s;o required to furni&s;h their quota of men to join with the other colo|nies in defending the frontiers of New-York in ca&s;e of an attack<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">The quotas of men to be furni&s;hed by each government for the defence of New-York, if attacked, were as follows, viz.
